}","git_refs_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/git/refs{/sha}","trees_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/git/trees{/sha}","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/statuses/{sha}","languages_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/languages","stargazers_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/stargazers","contributors_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/contributors","subscribers_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/subscribers","subscription_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/subscription","commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/commits{/sha}","git_commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/git/commits{/sha}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/comments{/number}","issue_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/comments{/number}","contents_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/contents/{+path}","compare_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/compare/{base}...{head}","merges_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/merges","archive_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/{archive_format}{/ref}","downloads_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/downloads","issues_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues{/number}","pulls_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/pulls{/number}","milestones_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/milestones{/number}","notifications_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/notifications{?since,all,participating}","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/labels{/name}","releases_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/releases{/id}","deployments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/deployments","created_at":"2013-04-18T15:24:53Z","updated_at":"2025-11-10T12:46:51Z","pushed_at":"2025-11-08T10:38:11Z","git_url":"git://github.com/glfw/glfw.git","ssh_url":"git@github.com:glfw/glfw.git","clone_url":"https://github.com/glfw/glfw.git","svn_url":"https://github.com/glfw/glfw","homepage":"https://www.glfw.org","size":17017,"stargazers_count":14356,"watchers_count":14356,"language":"C","has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":true,"has_pages":false,"has_discussions":false,"forks_count":5683,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":735,"license":{"key":"zlib","name":"zlib License","spdx_id":"Zlib","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/zlib","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTI3"},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":false,"topics":["c","linux","macos","opengl","opengl-es","unix","vulkan","windows"],"visibility":"public","forks":5683,"open_issues":735,"watchers":14356,"default_branch":"master","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"body":"Hello,\r\n\r\nA)\r\nThis code in win32_window.c:\r\n```\r\nvoid _glfwPlatformShowWindow(_GLFWwindow* window)\r\n{\r\n    ShowWindow(window->win32.handle, SW_SHOW);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe should be:\r\n```\r\nvoid _glfwPlatformShowWindow(_GLFWwindow* window)\r\n{\r\n    ShowWindow(window->win32.handle, SW_SHOWNA);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nRight now if you call `glfwCreateWindow()` with the `GLFW_FOCUSED` hint set to FALSE, the code in glfwCreateWindow does:\r\n```\r\n_glfwPlatformShowWindow(window);\r\nif (wndconfig.focused)\r\n    _glfwPlatformFocusWindow(window);\r\n```\r\nAnd _glfwPlatformShowWindow() alone with SW_SHOW \"activates\" the Windows. Now honestly, I am confused about the exact meaning of \"activation\" in the Win32 api but essentially it looks like we are losing the focus, and this defeat the purpose of GLFW_FOCUSED as documented:  `GLFW_FOCUSED specifies whether the windowed mode window will be given input focus when created. This hint is ignored for full screen and initially hidden windows. `\r\n\r\nI will post a PR shortly to make it easy to test that change. I think it should probably be checked/confirmed by people who are more expert of the Win32 api that I am. \r\n\r\n(PS/1: My usage context is I am trying to get this feature working in my GLFW backends: https://twitter.com/ocornut/status/950430111710482433 / the code create undecorated window dynamically and it is a problem and overly noticeable by the end-user if the parent window lose its focus.)\r\n\r\n(PS/2: Out of curiosity I traced the history for `_glfwPlatformShowWindow()`: \r\nMay 2014: b91116e2bc8e1abe83b2f486b9cb9b1f0fc1109b Changed `SW_SHOWNORMAL` to `SW_SHOW` for #264\r\nJan 2013: b72a97d5318ca497224739411d806bc4b217cc0d Refactor, didn't affect functionalities\r\nAug 2012, 596132c3a1becceb0ba6d10991d52a85ba8f201c Initial version)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nB)\r\nNote that my proposed PR only fixes glfwCreateWindow().\r\n`glfwShowWindow()` always calls `_glfwPlatformShowWindow` + `_glfwPlatformFocusWindow`, which seems redundant with the the fact that `glfwFocusWindow()` exists. \r\nMy intuition it that it would it be more correct and consistent to remove that call to `_glfwPlatformFocusWindow()` in `glfwShowWindow()`, however: that extra call was added in 89f438de5a862802717a5d6e32ebfe462775cccf \"Fix window focus regression\" (March 2016) so I imagine there is more to it.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\nThank you very much.\r\nO.\r\n  ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/1179/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/glfw/glfw/issues/1179/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed"}},"event":"cross-referenced"}]